The behavior of the function Fâ²(k) is as follows:
    For samples at k=0,2,4, . . . , exactly the cosine transform, C(k), is obtained; For samples at k=1,3,5, . . . , the minus cosine, âC(k), is obtained which is the DCT-I; In order to describe the Sine transform, the variable kâ² will be changed to j such that 
