In the example of FIG. 11B, negative focal lenses L(A) 2 and L(B) 2 are used for the further reduction of the length and volume of the system. This implementation also utilizes a demagnification factor that enables a reduced shearing interference length. In this case, if the lenses are still positioned in the same locations, the focusing is obtained at a distance of (âf2) relatively to the last lens. Thus, the total length L will be:

